        "title": "COST Action Meeting",
        "excerpt":"Thanks to an invitation by Pietro Olivieto, I recently participated in a COST Action meeting in Coimbra, Portugal. By definition COST is a European network for cooperating in science and technology and I have to admit, the name fits pretty well. This particular COST action is entitled “Improving Applicability of Nature-Inspired Optimisation by Joining Theory and Practice” and as a result, I’ve spend the last two days in meetings on “closing the gap” between theory and practice. ","categories": ["news"],
